# PROJECT UI/UX & DEVELOPMENT RULES
Stack: Next.js (App Router) + TailwindCSS + shadcn/ui

========================================================
1. CORE DESIGN PHILOSOPHY
========================================================

• Modern, minimal, brand-focused.
• Section-based, marketing-oriented layout.
• Products visually scannable.
• Clean but slightly casual UI.
• Avoid heavy gradients, complex effects.
• Use white space as a key tool.

Design Principles:
- Clarity
- Strong hierarchy
- Visual breathing room
- Large typography
- Grid consistency
- Soft interactions

========================================================
2. DESIGN SYSTEM RULES
========================================================

2.1 Spacing
8px base grid.
Scale: 4,8,12,16,24,32,48,64,96

Sections:
- Padding: py-24 desktop / py-16 mobile
- Gap: gap-12 or gap-16

2.2 Container Width
- max-w-7xl, mx-auto
- px-6 mobile / px-8 desktop

2.3 Border Radius
- Cards: rounded-2xl
- Buttons: rounded-xl
- Inputs: rounded-lg

2.4 Shadows
Soft only:
- shadow-sm
- shadow-md

2.5 Typography
Large, bold headlines.

H1: text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight  
H2: text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold  
H3: text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold  
Body: text-base md:text-lg text-muted-foreground

Avoid small text unless necessary.

========================================================
3. LAYOUT STRUCTURE RULES
========================================================

Page structure:

1. Hero  
2. Value Proposition  
3. Product Highlight  
4. Social Proof / Trust  
5. CTA  
6. Footer

Hero:
- Strong headline
- Short description (max 2 lines)
- Primary + Secondary CTA
- Visual/product image right (desktop)
- Stack vertically on mobile

Product Grid:
- 2 columns mobile, 3–4 desktop
- Equal card height
- Image top, title, short description, CTA button

========================================================
4. COMPONENT RULES (shadcn/ui)
========================================================

Use shadcn base components only.
Extend via className and variants.

Allowed:
- Button, Card, Input, Badge, Dialog, Sheet, Dropdown, Tabs, Accordion

Custom wrappers:
- Section, Container, ProductCard, FeatureCard, CTASection

No inline styles.
Use Tailwind classes only.

========================================================
5. COLOR SYSTEM
========================================================

Define in tailwind.config.

Use:
- Primary (brand)
- Neutral grayscale
- Soft accent background
- Muted text

Avoid:
- Excess accent colors
- High saturation combos

Buttons:
Primary → solid  
Secondary → outline  
Tertiary → ghost

========================================================
6. INTERACTION RULES
========================================================

Hover:
- Scale max 105%
- Subtle shadow increase
- Minimal color shift

Transitions:
- duration-200 or 300
- ease-in-out

No aggressive animations.
Keep motion subtle.

========================================================
7. RESPONSIVE RULES
========================================================

Mobile-first.
Breakpoints: sm, md, lg, xl

All components stack cleanly on mobile.

========================================================
8. UX RULES
========================================================

• Concise text.
• One message per section.
• Important content above fold.
• CTA at least twice per page.

Product priority:
Image > Name > Key Value > CTA

========================================================
9. PERFORMANCE RULES
========================================================

• Use Next.js Image.
• Avoid unnecessary client components.
• Default to server components.
• Lazy load heavy parts.
• Minimize bundle size.

========================================================
10. CODE STRUCTURE
========================================================

app/
  (marketing)/
    page.tsx
    components/
      Hero.tsx
      ProductGrid.tsx
      CTA.tsx
  layout.tsx

components/
  ui/ (shadcn)
  shared/
  marketing/

No logic in UI components.
Presentational only.

